1
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:04,179
.:: La Fabrique ::.
synced to Temple.Grandin.HBO

2
00:00:06,314 --> 00:00:08,115
My name is Temple Grandin.

3
00:00:08,816 --> 00:00:10,617
I'm not like other people.

4
00:00:15,116 --> 00:00:17,913
I think in pictures
and I connect them.

5
00:02:06,909 --> 00:02:08,537
There she is!
Temple!

6
00:02:10,760 --> 00:02:12,040
It's hot!

7
00:02:14,009 --> 00:02:17,005
Come on, dear. You're holding up
the other passengers!

8
00:02:18,676 --> 00:02:20,362
I can see the heat!

9
00:02:32,506 --> 00:02:34,092
Do people live here?

10
00:02:41,645 --> 00:02:43,167
The wolf is growling

11
00:02:43,858 --> 00:02:46,712
and the man with the shotgun
says to Illya Kuryakin,

12
00:02:46,837 --> 00:02:48,719
"Would you like for me
to open the gate?"

13
00:02:50,816 --> 00:02:52,870
I'm sorry, Temple, you lost me.

14
00:02:53,477 --> 00:02:56,175
"The man from U.N.C.L.E."
"The gazebo in the maze."

15
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,691
The wolf is growling

16
00:02:58,151 --> 00:03:00,569
and the man with the shotgun
says to Illya Kuryakin,

17
00:03:00,738 --> 00:03:02,698
<i>Would you like for me
to open the gate?</i>

18
00:03:03,823 --> 00:03:06,081
"Would you like for me
to open the gate?"

19
00:03:11,055 --> 00:03:12,055
You okay?

20
00:03:13,551 --> 00:03:15,320
Aunt Ann, what is this place?

21
00:03:16,094 --> 00:03:17,321
Just holding pens.

22
00:03:17,446 --> 00:03:19,765
You don't have those
on the east coast.

23
00:03:20,034 --> 00:03:21,814
Is this where they slaughter them?

24
00:03:23,540 --> 00:03:24,590
Yes, it is.

25
00:03:31,234 --> 00:03:32,951
"Would you like for me
to open the gate?"

26
00:03:34,440 --> 00:03:36,779
"Would you like for me
to open the gate?"

27
00:03:37,443 --> 00:03:38,846
Yes. Yes, please.

28
00:03:40,182 --> 00:03:42,040
Open the gate, please, Temple?

29
00:03:44,086 --> 00:03:46,007
Would you like for me
to open that gate?

30
00:04:27,590 --> 00:04:28,889
Come on, Temple.

31
00:04:53,775 --> 00:04:55,275
Temple made it okay.

32
00:04:56,185 --> 00:04:58,563
- Say hi to your uncle Mike.
- Hi, Temple.

33
00:04:59,482 --> 00:05:02,126
I just been tellin' Billy here
all about our summer visitor.

34
00:05:05,089 --> 00:05:06,591
Are you a cowboy?

35
00:05:06,876 --> 00:05:08,135
Excuse my niece.

36
00:05:08,303 --> 00:05:11,431
That's not how we greet people.
You know better than that.

37
00:05:12,467 --> 00:05:14,413
Hello, I'm Temple.
It's very nice to meet you.

38
00:05:14,538 --> 00:05:16,808
Hello, I'm Temple.
It's very nice to meet you.

39
00:05:17,566 --> 00:05:18,993
Nice to meet you too.

40
00:05:22,116 --> 00:05:22,976
Ma'am.

41
00:05:24,302 --> 00:05:26,515
Thanks for this.
I'll replace it tomorrow.

42
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:27,991
No rush. I got spares.

43
00:05:32,087 --> 00:05:33,797
Do you get
"the man from U.N.C.L.E."?

44
00:05:35,009 --> 00:05:36,593
Let me show you your room.

45
00:05:45,491 --> 00:05:46,524
These okay here?

46
00:05:50,073 --> 00:05:51,908
All my science fiction books
are there.

47
00:05:52,076 --> 00:05:54,992
- How do I know this is my room?
- Because we say so.

48
00:05:55,561 --> 00:05:56,738
It's your room.

49
00:06:34,180 --> 00:06:36,891
So, you excited about college?

50
00:06:37,261 --> 00:06:38,394
That's something.

51
00:06:39,479 --> 00:06:40,425
Thank you.

52
00:06:40,672 --> 00:06:43,199
I can't eat that. I have colitis.
I get it from nervousness.

53
00:06:43,324 --> 00:06:45,239
- I eat pudding and jell-o.
- I know.

54
00:06:45,905 --> 00:06:47,064
Your mom said.

55
00:06:51,207 --> 00:06:53,397
So you didn't answer
Mike's question.

56
00:06:53,724 --> 00:06:55,382
Are you excited
about going to college?

57
00:06:55,507 --> 00:06:58,569
I want to stay in high school.
I like my science teacher.

58
00:06:59,051 --> 00:07:01,319
Dr. Carlock's very smart
and he's been to college.

59
00:07:01,444 --> 00:07:04,984
So I don't understand why I have to move
to learn what he probably already knows.

60
00:07:12,695 --> 00:07:14,959
The desert spoons and teaspoons
go in different sections.

61
00:07:15,085 --> 00:07:16,220
I did that.

62
00:07:19,539 --> 00:07:21,438
Your uncle can't tell them apart.

63
00:07:21,563 --> 00:07:23,441
And sometimes I can't either.

64
00:07:26,125 --> 00:07:27,500
They're different.

65
00:07:28,980 --> 00:07:30,116
Yes, they are.

66
00:07:31,266 --> 00:07:33,194
I think it's time for bed,
young lady.

67
00:07:33,319 --> 00:07:35,329
We get up with the rooster
around here.

68
00:07:48,635 --> 00:07:50,086
You got everything?

69
00:07:50,552 --> 00:07:51,877
This is my room.

70
00:07:54,508 --> 00:07:55,511
Yes, it is.

71
00:07:56,408 --> 00:07:58,309
- So good night.
- I don't want you to do that.

72
00:07:58,434 --> 00:08:00,794
I'm sorry. I forgot.
No hugs.

73
00:08:03,396 --> 00:08:04,625
Good night then.

74
00:08:50,683 --> 00:08:51,519
Hello?

75
00:08:51,644 --> 00:08:53,990
- <i>Did I wake you?</i>
- Of course not.

76
00:08:54,115 --> 00:08:55,513
- Who is it?
- It's Ann!

77
00:08:57,187 --> 00:09:00,438
Guess what I found balled up in
the bottom of Temple's closet?

78
00:09:00,732 --> 00:09:02,894
A lovely summer frock
she didn't want?

79
00:09:03,780 --> 00:09:05,674
It's taken me an age to iron it.

80
00:09:05,799 --> 00:09:07,239
I'll mail it in the morning.

81
00:09:07,407 --> 00:09:09,868
<i>You couldn't get her to pack it,
not sure I can get her to wear it.</i>

82
00:09:10,037 --> 00:09:12,289
The other one came off
the minute she arrived.

83
00:09:12,457 --> 00:09:13,497
How is she?

84
00:09:15,198 --> 00:09:16,384
She's good.

85
00:09:17,135 --> 00:09:18,027
Tell me.

86
00:09:19,327 --> 00:09:20,161
She...

87
00:09:21,255 --> 00:09:24,143
She got tense
when Mike mentioned college,

88
00:09:24,636 --> 00:09:26,096
but then she calmed down

89
00:09:26,221 --> 00:09:28,108
and she went off to bed just fine.

90
00:09:28,559 --> 00:09:29,815
Stop worrying.

91
00:09:29,983 --> 00:09:31,619
Temple's my job for the summer.

92
00:09:31,744 --> 00:09:33,362
Worry about the others.

93
00:09:33,765 --> 00:09:35,889
I'm sure
she's gonna have a great time.

94
00:09:36,197 --> 00:09:37,801
You do remember, though,

95
00:09:38,521 --> 00:09:40,522
something's gonna set her off.

96
00:09:58,130 --> 00:10:00,181
I could really use a hand here!

97
00:10:07,375 --> 00:10:09,636
So any idea
what your major might be?

98
00:10:09,895 --> 00:10:12,408
Science. Probably psychology.

99
00:10:14,801 --> 00:10:16,913
You don't have to decide just yet,
do you?

100
00:10:17,172 --> 00:10:19,886
- It's better than boarding school.
- That's great.

101
00:10:20,011 --> 00:10:22,476
- Lots of choices.
- Danny's looking at you.

102
00:10:22,644 --> 00:10:25,269
He can see all around
without moving his head.

103
00:10:26,359 --> 00:10:29,069
- So how do you know where he's looking?
- His ears.

104
00:10:29,237 --> 00:10:31,227
He points his ears
where he's looking.

105
00:10:31,574 --> 00:10:33,972
See?
He's lookin' at you, aunt.

106
00:10:34,245 --> 00:10:36,243
And he's lookin' at those cowboys.

107
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:40,029
See? Now I got his attention.
Now he's looking at me.

108
00:10:40,769 --> 00:10:41,845
You're right.

109
00:10:42,112 --> 00:10:43,746
How'd you figure that out?

110
00:10:47,932 --> 00:10:49,433
What are they doing?

111
00:11:03,956 --> 00:11:05,407
What is this thing?

112
00:11:06,392 --> 00:11:08,669
It holds her still
so Billy can inoculate her.

113
00:11:33,102 --> 00:11:35,453
What happened to it?
It calmed down.

114
00:11:36,551 --> 00:11:37,887
They just like it.

115
00:11:38,012 --> 00:11:39,239
It gentles 'em.

116
00:12:36,093 --> 00:12:37,928
Stand still and they'll come to you.

117
00:12:38,831 --> 00:12:40,681
Won't harm you.
Just curious.

118
00:12:41,779 --> 00:12:43,380
Can't help themselves.

119
00:13:24,114 --> 00:13:26,546
Are you worried about
keeping up with the other students?

120
00:13:27,544 --> 00:13:30,023
- I'm not stupid.
- I didn't say you were.

121
00:13:30,148 --> 00:13:32,986
- Is it moving away from home?
- Hold it straighter.

122
00:13:35,859 --> 00:13:37,853
Why don't you want to go to college?

123
00:13:39,897 --> 00:13:40,741
People.

124
00:13:41,675 --> 00:13:43,370
I don't understand people.

125
00:13:43,495 --> 00:13:45,758
At least the people at school
know I don't understand them

126
00:13:45,883 --> 00:13:47,617
and some of them
are my friends anyway.

127
00:13:47,742 --> 00:13:49,454
What don't you understand?

128
00:13:50,130 --> 00:13:51,967
Girls get all goofy over boys.

129
00:13:54,375 --> 00:13:57,073
They talk about silly pop groups
and clothes and say things like,

130
00:13:57,199 --> 00:13:59,085
"why are you so grumpy?"
When I'm happy.

131
00:13:59,211 --> 00:14:01,980
And I say, "I'm happy". And they say,
"You don't look happy".

132
00:14:02,105 --> 00:14:04,014
And I say,
"Can't you see I'm thinking?

133
00:14:04,182 --> 00:14:05,938
And can't you see I'm sad?"

134
00:14:06,837 --> 00:14:09,384
And I don't know
what they're talking about.

135
00:14:10,468 --> 00:14:12,155
What do you look like
when you're happy?

136
00:14:13,089 --> 00:14:14,142
Like this.

137
00:14:15,113 --> 00:14:17,510
No, you didn't look like that
when you were telling me about

138
00:14:17,636 --> 00:14:20,230
"the man from U.N.C.L.E."
You looked like this...

139
00:14:25,098 --> 00:14:26,428
That's funny lookin'.

140
00:14:28,104 --> 00:14:28,842
Happy.</i>

141
00:14:29,719 --> 00:14:31,176
And that's you angry.

142
00:14:36,857 --> 00:14:37,708
Angry.

143
00:14:40,772 --> 00:14:41,565
Happy.

144
00:14:42,032 --> 00:14:43,388
I'm happy in that one.

145
00:14:44,445 --> 00:14:46,251
I'd say more satisfied.

146
00:14:48,006 --> 00:14:48,975
Satisfied.

147
00:15:16,824 --> 00:15:19,296
Maria, can you give me a hand here?

148
00:16:31,987 --> 00:16:33,256
Close it on me.

149
00:16:34,090 --> 00:16:36,295
- Let's get you out of...
- Close it on me!

150
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:38,654
- Don't be silly!
- Please!

151
00:16:50,697 --> 00:16:52,768
Close the sides.
Close the sides.

152
00:16:54,580 --> 00:16:55,727
Please!

153
00:17:01,965 --> 00:17:03,609
Harder! More!

154
00:18:15,531 --> 00:18:17,476
Did you see Temple's handiwork
at the gate?

155
00:18:17,602 --> 00:18:19,602
Isn't that the darndest thing?

156
00:18:24,446 --> 00:18:25,318
Hi, darlin'.

157
00:18:26,319 --> 00:18:29,644
All these years Ann's been bugging me.
Like I could ever come up with that!

158
00:18:36,370 --> 00:18:37,486
Is that it?

159
00:18:38,964 --> 00:18:40,724
Is that what Temple's been using?

160
00:18:40,978 --> 00:18:42,162
Yes, it is.

161
00:18:42,940 --> 00:18:44,580
I know, it looks horrible,

162
00:18:45,147 --> 00:18:46,392
but it helps her.

163
00:18:51,719 --> 00:18:53,264
I'll go find Temple.

164
00:18:59,897 --> 00:19:01,622
That's mine.
That's Temple's.

165
00:19:01,980 --> 00:19:05,288
She's had a great summer.
You won't believe what she's fixed.

166
00:19:05,413 --> 00:19:07,283
She's wonderful with the cattle.

167
00:19:07,633 --> 00:19:08,718
I appreciate that.

168
00:19:08,844 --> 00:19:11,256
I should warn you,
she has her mind set on staying.

169
00:19:12,014 --> 00:19:13,515
That's not an option.

170
00:19:20,693 --> 00:19:22,999
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to attack you,

171
00:19:24,168 --> 00:19:26,742
especially when you've been
so generous all summer.

172
00:19:53,499 --> 00:19:55,369
How was your trip, mother?
You made good time.

173
00:19:57,483 --> 00:19:58,660
It was long.

174
00:19:59,811 --> 00:20:01,245
Thank you for asking.

175
00:20:02,887 --> 00:20:04,488
You ready for college?

176
00:20:07,698 --> 00:20:09,744
I think I'd rather stay here.

177
00:20:11,137 --> 00:20:12,812
We've talked about this.

178
00:20:13,409 --> 00:20:15,528
Sweetheart, you're gonna be fine.

179
00:20:17,778 --> 00:20:19,200
No one expected it.

180
00:20:19,667 --> 00:20:21,366
It's nothin' short of a miracle.

181
00:20:24,047 --> 00:20:25,391
It's a miracle!

182
00:20:31,716 --> 00:20:33,542
{\Franklin Pierce College
1966}

183
00:20:43,160 --> 00:20:44,161
This way.

184
00:20:55,352 --> 00:20:57,599
- Can I get that for you?
- Thank you.

185
00:21:21,833 --> 00:21:24,230
224.
This is you.

186
00:21:33,359 --> 00:21:34,768
I don't have a roommate.

187
00:21:35,453 --> 00:21:38,341
Your roommate is coming
in another couple of weeks.

188
00:21:38,902 --> 00:21:40,012
Remember?

189
00:21:41,306 --> 00:21:43,073
Everyone else has a roommate!

190
00:21:43,407 --> 00:21:47,239
Why don't you just think of it
as a chance to settle in, sweetheart?

191
00:21:48,872 --> 00:21:50,958
Then I'll go back home!

192
00:21:51,126 --> 00:21:53,670
I know that this
is strange and new,

193
00:21:54,441 --> 00:21:57,050
- but you're going to be all right.
- I don't want to stay here!

194
00:21:57,545 --> 00:21:58,914
Try and stay calm.

195
00:21:59,805 --> 00:22:03,226
It's all right.
Try and calm down, all right?

196
00:22:03,508 --> 00:22:06,209
I'm going to give you
a moment to yourself.

197
00:22:19,239 --> 00:22:21,115
- What's wrong?
- Is she all right?

198
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:23,700
Interested in playing
with other children?

199
00:22:24,382 --> 00:22:25,632
No, not really.

200
00:22:26,558 --> 00:22:28,259
Plays with toys, dolls?

201
00:22:28,890 --> 00:22:30,756
She loves to rip things.

202
00:22:31,315 --> 00:22:33,527
And no speech yet at the age of?

203
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:34,921
Four.

204
00:22:35,278 --> 00:22:36,191
She's four.

205
00:22:39,155 --> 00:22:40,030
Not yet.

206
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:45,611
I'm sure it's just a phase, but...

207
00:22:45,736 --> 00:22:47,955
Your child is clearly autistic.

208
00:22:50,292 --> 00:22:51,230
Autistic.

209
00:22:51,355 --> 00:22:54,683
- I'm not familiar...
- She's an infantile schizophrenic.

210
00:22:57,471 --> 00:22:58,471
Infantile?

211
00:23:01,148 --> 00:23:03,109
So when would she grow out of it?

212
00:23:03,234 --> 00:23:05,782
I mean, what's the next step for...

213
00:23:05,986 --> 00:23:08,512
We generally recommend
an institution.

214
00:23:09,313 --> 00:23:10,442
For how long?

215
00:23:10,785 --> 00:23:12,877
I'm not sure I would like that.
I really...

216
00:23:13,003 --> 00:23:16,888
- I wouldn't wanna miss her first words.
- She probably will never speak.

217
00:23:17,984 --> 00:23:20,593
And I'm afraid
there is no course of treatment.

218
00:23:21,034 --> 00:23:23,559
I'm talking about
institutionalization.

219
00:23:26,945 --> 00:23:27,946
But...

220
00:23:30,736 --> 00:23:32,855
She was a perfectly normal baby

221
00:23:32,980 --> 00:23:34,922
and then later she changed.

222
00:23:35,158 --> 00:23:38,058
So I need to know how, why.

223
00:23:39,485 --> 00:23:42,878
I'm not sure you'd... Perhaps
if you had your husband call me.

224
00:23:43,208 --> 00:23:45,794
My husband is a very busy man
and I graduated from Harvard,

225
00:23:45,919 --> 00:23:47,619
so why don't you try me?

226
00:23:48,814 --> 00:23:49,814
I'm sorry.

227
00:23:52,130 --> 00:23:54,781
It's been suggested that it may be

228
00:23:54,906 --> 00:23:56,811
a lack of bonding with the mother...

229
00:23:57,363 --> 00:24:01,369
That at a crucial phase,
the mother was cold, aloof,

230
00:24:02,237 --> 00:24:04,596
when the child most needed
physical affection.

231
00:24:04,721 --> 00:24:06,408
But that is not what happened.

232
00:24:06,533 --> 00:24:08,693
We have another child
and she is not like this

233
00:24:08,818 --> 00:24:10,969
and I did not do anything different.

234
00:24:11,449 --> 00:24:12,990
Temple rejects me.

235
00:24:13,115 --> 00:24:15,547
I want to hug her
and she won't let me.

236
00:24:16,200 --> 00:24:18,384
I'm supposed to have done this.
Then I can undo it.

237
00:24:18,709 --> 00:24:21,328
- You just tell me what to do.
- As I said,

238
00:24:21,453 --> 00:24:23,657
I recommend institutionalization.

239
00:24:24,436 --> 00:24:26,563
Here is a list of facilities
that we recommend.

240
00:24:28,358 --> 00:24:29,888
Dah-og.

241
00:24:32,892 --> 00:24:33,893
Temple.

242
00:24:34,100 --> 00:24:35,101
Dog.

243
00:24:42,224 --> 00:24:44,107
Cah-at.

244
00:24:44,746 --> 00:24:45,747
Cat.

245
00:24:46,088 --> 00:24:47,188
Temple, try.

246
00:24:50,268 --> 00:24:51,363
Mah...

247
00:24:52,820 --> 00:24:53,941
... me.

248
00:24:55,233 --> 00:24:56,464
Mom...

249
00:24:58,824 --> 00:25:00,364
I know you can hear me.

250
00:25:04,729 --> 00:25:05,730
All right.

251
00:25:06,988 --> 00:25:09,539
I think mommy needs
a five-minute break.

252
00:25:50,345 --> 00:25:53,204
<i>Avez-vous lu la page, Mlle Grandin?</i>

253
00:25:55,070 --> 00:25:57,817
I don't want to study French.
I want to learn science.

254
00:26:01,674 --> 00:26:03,340
Read the page, please.

255
00:26:06,498 --> 00:26:07,499
Read it.

256
00:26:14,587 --> 00:26:16,416
And what did it say?

257
00:26:19,494 --> 00:26:23,195
<i>"Jean-Paul Sartre
naît le 21 juin 1905,</i>

258
00:26:23,363 --> 00:26:24,390
<i>à Paris;</i>

